New German warship delayed again
The German Navy’s newest frigate should be handed over in 2014 to replace aging Cold War warships, but it won’t be due to system failure and rapidly rising costs until at least next year, local media reported.
The handover of the ship “Rheinland-Pfalz”, the flagship of the new class of frigate Baden-Wuerttemberg, is now postponed to the first half of 2019, according to the newspaper Die Zeit, citing a military official.
