2004: A major earthquake off the west coast of Indonesia's Aceh province in northern Sumatra on December 26 caused a tsunami that struck 14 countries and killed 226,000 people along the coast of India, more than half of them in Aceh.
2005: A series of strong earthquakes hit western Sumatra in late March and early April.
Hundreds of people died on the island of Nias off the coast of Sumatra.
