2009: A magnitude 7.6 earthquake occurred near the city of Padang, the capital of West Sumatra province.
More than 1,100 people died.
2010: A 7.5-magnitude earthquake struck one of the Mentawai Islands and triggered a tsunami up to 10 meters high, destroying dozens of villages and causing the deaths of about 300 people.
2016: A shallow earthquake hit the regency of Pidie Jay in Aceh and caused death and panic when people remembered the deadly 2004 earthquake and tsunami.
